01:12:39.130 --> 01:12:39.990
this time.

01:12:39.990 --> 01:12:41.770
But we'll do some
more in a minute.

01:12:41.770 --> 01:12:46.900
So say Will picked--
say he picked C.

01:12:46.900 --> 01:12:52.000
And say that then I
will pick B. All right,

01:12:52.000 --> 01:12:55.220
so on C, there's three choices.

01:12:55.220 --> 01:12:55.830
3.

01:12:55.830 --> 01:12:57.480
4, and 8.

01:12:57.480 --> 01:13:01.775
And then, on my choice of
B, there's 1, 5, and 9.

01:13:06.160 --> 01:13:09.120
All right, so I get 1, 5, and 9.

01:13:09.120 --> 01:13:12.070
And now we can
see who wins here.

01:13:12.070 --> 01:13:17.810
Well, C wins there,
loses here, loses there.

01:13:17.810 --> 01:13:22.370
C wins here, and B
wins the next two.

01:13:22.370 --> 01:13:24.000
And C wins these.

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:26.650
And B wins the tiebreaker.

01:13:26.650 --> 01:13:30.280
So B beats C with
probability 5/9.

01:13:38.420 --> 01:13:38.920
All right.

01:13:38.920 --> 01:13:43.650
So you don't want to pick
A, you don't want to pick C,

01:13:43.650 --> 01:13:45.094
you want to try a bet with B?

01:13:48.363 --> 01:13:52.840
I mean, look, you've got B
beats C. We just showed that.

01:13:52.840 --> 01:13:57.847
C beats A. I mean, that's a
